Just a comment re the cook from Union City's review: it's been said a hundred times over, but apparently, it still needs repeating-- if your fish smells or tastes "fishy", it is not fresh! Fish should have the pleasant, briny aroma of the sea. It should never smell or taste bad. No recipe will mask less than stellar seafood. I urge you to find a reputable fishmonger (with a very high turnover) and make this recipe again using only the best ingredients-- you will be amazed at the difference in taste! By the way, I make this recipe whenver we get a hankering for salmon, and it's great. I love the sweet/hot combination!

