Rating: 4
I could not believe how FAST this was to make!!! I plan to make this for my inlaws over Labor Day; very yummy and impressive, despite only 5 ingredients!!! I used the fillets, we will use steaks next time for ease of grilling. Also, when I tasted the glaze "raw" you could taste the heat of the mustard, so I didn't use all the mustard the recipe calls for (full strength). But I would add the full mustard b/c it's not as strong with the vinegar added or after cooking. Also, definitely double the sauce, and save more of it for serving rather than basting. Overall, a definite keeper! I also added a little ginger, and I served it over rice and steamed broccoli. (The rice took longer than the salmon to make!!)

